1
00:00:59,040 --> 00:00:59,600
Qi Yi.

2
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,370
You're here.

3
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:11,400
I thought you weren't coming.

4
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,890
Let's go sit over there.

5
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,640
What you said last time,

6
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:39,100
I went back and thought about it a lot.

7
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,360
I feel I need to explain it to you.

8
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,000
Of course,

9
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,200
from the very beginning,

10
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,060
I couldn't wait to get to know you.

11
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,840
Every time you came to the imperial kiln,

12
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,700
I volunteered to show you around.

13
00:01:56,759 --> 00:01:57,759
Not long after we met,

14
00:01:57,759 --> 00:01:59,320
I confessed to you in a rush.

15
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,140
Did I scare you?

16
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,600
But I'm not like this with everyone.

17
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,200
You like history

18
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,940
and cultural relics just like me,

19
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,820
and you're so understanding.

20
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,880
When I was nervous about my interview,

21
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,740
you were the one who cheered me on.

22
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,840
But you know what?

23
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,840
Those aren't the reasons I like you.

24
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,420
I can't explain why I like you.

25
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,600
I only know

26
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:33,360
that such a strong feeling

27
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,420
is something I have

28
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,160
never had before.

29
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,440
I thought,

30
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:47,000
since it's so rare to meet someone I like this much,

31
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:49,040
if I didn't say it out loud,

32
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,770
it would be a great pity.

33
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,760
I didn't know how to tell you.

34
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,530
Actually...

35
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,960
I practiced at home for a long time that day.

36
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:04,220
When I told you I liked you,

37
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,880
I was really nervous.

38
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:13,010
I can't tell exactly why I like you.

39
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,040
I just

40
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,600
know this feeling is quite strong.

41
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,760
I like everything about you.

42
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,000
Like I said,

43
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,240
if you feel

44
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,090
the timing isn't right yet,

45
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,880
I can step back.

46
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:35,760
We can

47
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,690
continue to be friends.

48
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,280
That day,

49
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:42,940
when I asked

50
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:45,120
if we could date,

51
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,000
that was my truest feeling at the time.

52
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,920
Actually,

53
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,840
you can ask me again.

54
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,280
Then I'll ask you,

55
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,160
will you date me?

56
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,560
I've told you so many times

57
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,840
that you shouldn't eat

58
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,800
that junk food from outside.

59
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,800
But you just wouldn't listen.

60
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,000
Now you know the pain.

61
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:07,660
Come on,

62
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,640
take your medicine.

63
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,160
Come on.

64
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,520
Slowly now.

65
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,260
Did you swallow it?

66
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,400
You've always been in poor health,

67
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,440
and I'm the one who takes care of you.

68
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:19,280
I know your constitution

69
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,340
better than you do.

70
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,760
So you have to listen to me.

71
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:22,520
Got it?

72
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:23,810
Let me

73
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,080
feel if you have a fever.

74
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:27,480
Let me take your temperature.

75
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,280
No need, Mom.

76
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:30,000
I'll be fine after lying down for a while.

77
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,880
Did the whole class go out this weekend?

78
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:32,760
Why did you go eat?

79
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:33,560
Who was there?

80
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,480
Aunt,

81
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,200
my mom wants you to go for a walk with her.

82
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,159
What walk?

83
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,800
Your sister is in so much pain.

84
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,320
Mom, just go.

85
00:05:42,159 --> 00:05:43,080
I knew it.

86
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:43,920
Both of you

87
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,320
think I'm nagging and annoying,

88
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:46,780
and you won't listen to me.

89
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:47,760
No.

90
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,650
Are you really okay?

91
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,200
Alright.

92
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,240
I'm going out then.

93
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:53,760
Let's go.

94
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,220
Don't bother your sister.

95
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,080
Call me if you need anything.

96
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:18,650
Morning.

97
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,000
Morning.

98
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,770
I bought breakfast for you.

99
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,080
Is your stomach feeling better?

100
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,560
Didn't I tell you to rest at home a bit longer?

101
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:39,690
I want to finish it as soon as possible.

102
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,040
Cencen,

103
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,320
you're out.

104
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,460
Sister went to school to do extracurricular assignments.

105
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,720
She went out early in the morning

106
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,250
without eating breakfast.

107
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,360
Maybe she ate out.

108
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,400
Eating out?

109
00:07:59,400 --> 00:07:59,860
Well...

110
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,080
Breakfast is ready at home, but she didn't eat here.

111
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:02,740
Eating out?

112
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,860
She only knows how to waste money.

113
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,130
The shape is beautiful,

114
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,700
and the color is also nice.

115
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,380
I didn't expect Guan Lin to have such skills.

116
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,860
I don't understand either

117
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,920
why Mr. Wei isn't satisfied with it.

118
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,320
Everything I do is wrong.

119
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,180
I can see it too.

120
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,970
You just don't plan to teach me.

121
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:26,720
Right.

122
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,520
When I die,

123
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,490
I'd rather tear down this kiln.

124
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,880
But I'm your only apprentice.

125
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,850
Bullying me for being childless, huh?

126
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,120
You think you can control me?

127
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,440
I didn't mean that.

128
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:39,320
Master.

129
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,720
Don't call me Master.

130
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,039
I don't deserve it.

131
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:42,500
Mr. Wei.

132
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,240
No. I don't deserve to be your master.

133
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,680
Don't lower yourself to his level.

134
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,920
Don't be angry, Mr. Wei.

135
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:47,200
No.

136
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:47,640
Let's go sit over there.

137
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,000
Can you be reasonable, Master?

138
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,080
Now he thinks he's so capable.

139
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,920
Don't be angry.

140
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:52,120
Please don't be angry, Mr. Wei.

141
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:52,920
Please calm down.

142
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:53,480
Come, come.

143
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,880
Fine. You're so capable.

144
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:55,800
Calm down.

145
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:57,220
Master Wei,

146
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,680
you've finally recovered well.

147
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,080
Please don't get angry.

148
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,080
Yeah, Master Wei.

149
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,490
Please don't get angry.

150
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,060
Why are you here again?

151
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:10,540
Master Wei.

152
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,130
Here,

153
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,570
Mr. Wei, take a look.

154
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:22,210
Look, 'Spring brings good fortune and harmony.'

155
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,000
Good craftsmanship.

156
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:36,360
I mean your restoration skills are quite good.

157
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,460
Thank you, Mr. Wei.

158
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,770
This porcelain made by Guan Lin

159
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:45,250
was fired in the newly built Chai Kiln.

160
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,720
It really can't compare to those fired in the old kiln.

161
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,800
At the time, we were only focused on

162
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,120
its shape and color,

163
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,000
and ignored its smoothness.

164
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:57,240
Young people want to run before they can walk.

165
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,200
Forget it.

166
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,650
You guys go back.

167
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,330
Take this vase with you too.

168
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:08,520
What?

169
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,850
Is there anything else?

170
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,800
How I teach my apprentices

171
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,960
is none of your business.

172
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:21,480
Brother Guan Lin.

173
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,920
You spend all day ignoring this excellent

174
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,960
and widely envied Wei Kiln instead of studying it.

175
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:27,320
Thinking about how to fire new porcelain all day.

176
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,600
Could it be that you're outside,

177
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,000
using Mr. Wei's name,

178
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,680
and secretly taking private jobs?

179
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:32,680
I didn't.

180
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,040
I have never used my master's title.

181
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,600
Yuexin.

182
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,840
You just complain that Mr. Wei doesn't teach you anything,

183
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,240
and you're planning to go out and start your own business.

184
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:41,680
Right?

185
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,320
I'm not that kind of person.

186
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,160
The day my master brought me back from the street,

187
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:46,600
I swore to the God of Kilns Tong Bin

188
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,640
that I would follow my master until I die.

189
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:49,680
But you didn't expect

190
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,840
that I could live this long, did you?

191
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,840
Master, can we be reasonable?

192
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,080
The new type of kiln and the Weijiayao kiln

193
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,040
don't conflict.

194
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,120
Now the small Chai Kiln outside,

195
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:57,880
electric kilns, and microwave kilns

196
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,540
are the choices for many small-scale products.

197
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,600
I haven't abandoned tradition.

198
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:05,360
Guan Lin.

199
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,120
Mr. Wei.

200
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,330
The old kiln is indeed good.

201
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,400
But firing one kiln

202
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,680
also consumes nearly two thousand catties of pine wood.

203
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,520
The cost is nearly a hundred thousand.

204
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,640
It's not that many people don't want to fire it,

205
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,000
but

206
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,280
they really can't afford it.

207
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,840
The master has watched the fire for thousands of years,

208
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,960
but when it comes to you,

209
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,440
it becomes touching a switch.

210
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,370
Then what's the point of using you?

211
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:27,800
I...

212
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,400
Mr. Wei.

213
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,040
I brought some materials,

214
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:31,700
take a look.

215
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,920
In the long river of history,

216
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:36,120
new types of kilns didn't come out of nowhere.

217
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,600
Although Weijiayao is

218
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,530
an old kiln to us,

219
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,960
it was also an innovation back then.

220
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,680
The development of skills

221
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:45,600
will definitely bring about the development of kilns.

222
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,930
All choices are determined by the market.

223
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,480
So many people choosing Weijiayao

224
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,320
has already proven

225
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,720
its own existence value.

226
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:07,860
Where is the character 'Xu' you made before?

227
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,320
Right here.

228
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:11,080
Character 'Xu'.

229
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:13,900
I remember writing it.

230
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,560
Does this look a bit like you?

231
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:16,280
Like me?

232
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,140
Maybe a little bit.

233
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,320
Does this look even more like it?

234
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,600
No, this one looks more like me.

235
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,720
This one looks like it.

236
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,520
This one looks like it.

237
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,680
The eyes on this one are open.

238
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:29,680
This one only looks like you with the eyes closed.

239
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:30,120
Okay.

240
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,490
This one looks like you.

241
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:34,980
No, it doesn't.

242
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,160
Before,

243
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,940
you always did things I like to do.

244
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:43,970
Do you have anything you like to do?

245
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:46,120
You can tell me anything.

246
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,760
Things I like to do?

247
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,120
Claw machine.

248
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:54,440
Claw machine.

249
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:55,690
Is it fun?

250
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:56,440
Yes, it is.

251
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,970
Go with me next time.

252
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,640
Let's not wait for next time.

253
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:02,770
Let's go after work.

254
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:03,720
Okay.

255
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,120
Want to challenge again?

256
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,520
That's great.

257
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:40,980
My mom and aunt are at home.

258
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,120
You should go back.

259
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,000
I'm sorry.

260
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,560
Am I an unqualified girlfriend?

261
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,240
Cencen, stop looking at your phone.

262
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,040
Go help your aunt serve the dishes.

263
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:49,480
Okay.

264
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:52,840
Aunt, let me help you.

265
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:55,120
Okay. Take this dish in.

266
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:02,680
Xiaocen.

267
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,560
I made your favorite shredded potatoes.

268
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,440
Thank you, Aunt.

269
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,370
You're welcome.

270
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:08,440
Want a drink?

271
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,100
No, thanks.

272
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,080
Here, sis.

273
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:26,840
Master,

274
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,000
are you sure you want to take this order?

275
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,840
I looked at this batch of porcelain.

276
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,680
It'll take at least two or three days to fire the kiln.

277
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,800
I'm worried about your health.

278
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,320
What if something happens...

279
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,120
You think I can't do it?

280
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,520
No, Master.

281
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,840
Do you think it's possible

282
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:43,760
that

283
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,140
I do the firing,

284
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:45,800
and you

285
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,520
supervise and guide me from the side?

286
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:47,920
You...

287
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,240
You do the firing?

288
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:50,360
Yeah.

289
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:53,130
Have you completed your apprenticeship?

290
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:53,880
Enough.

291
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,240
This order,

292
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,740
I've decided on it.

293
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:57,930
I have the final say.

294
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:58,960
Go.

295
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,960
Fortunately,

296
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,560
I came to Jingdezhen.

297
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:08,880
And luckily,

298
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:12,160
I came to Fuliang because of Weijiayao.

299
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,360
Otherwise, I wouldn't have seen such beautiful scenery.

300
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:17,760
During the Tang Dynasty,

301
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:20,280
Fuliang became the national porcelain-making center.

302
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:21,560
It's said that at that time,

303
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:23,200
craftsmen gathered from everywhere,

304
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,200
and kiln fires burned day and night.

305
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,360
Yaoli's glaze

306
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:28,240
and Fuliang's Kaolin Clay

307
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,440
were discovered here

308
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,620
and fired into porcelain.

309
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:33,800
Xu Xiao.

310
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,280
Sometimes I feel like

311
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,420
you are someone from the past.

312
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:45,320
Haven't you ever thought about going out to see the world?

313
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:46,410
Where to?

314
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,080
Like,

315
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:51,560
my hometown.

316
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,080
Of course.

317
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:56,480
I've always wanted to go

318
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:58,080
to the place where you grew up

319
00:15:58,320 --> 00:15:59,120
to take a look.

320
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:02,720
At first,

321
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,920
when I came to Jingdezhen,

322
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,040
I wasn't quite used to it.

323
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:08,560
First,

324
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:11,480
I was mad at myself for not doing well in the exams.

325
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,120
Second,

326
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:15,780
this place is indeed quite different from my hometown.

327
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:16,520
Really.

328
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:18,920
When school was about to start,

329
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,250
I kept dragging my feet.

330
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:23,520
But my mom had already arranged everything for me.

331
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:25,560
But now I really like it here.

332
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:27,810
I've fallen in love with

333
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,250
every blade of grass and tree here.

334
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,880
And everyone here.

335
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:10,640
I'm sorry.

336
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:12,560
I didn't know.

337
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:17,119
I...

338
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:18,530
Let's go.

339
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:32,170
Here,

340
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:34,880
it's wrong,

341
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:36,280
got it?

342
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,440
Practice this part again.

343
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:40,960
Xiaocen.

344
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,840
Why are you back so late again?

345
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,160
I went to Weijiayao.

346
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,720
Weijiayao is so far away.

347
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:51,600
Why did the professors assign you

348
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,880
so many extracurricular activities recently?

349
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,840
It's good to take practical classes.

350
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:56,680
You can make some

351
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:57,880
friends with common interests.

352
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:58,840
Isn't that nice?

353
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:00,720
Having enough credits is fine.

354
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,280
Why do you need so many credits?

355
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:03,320
But Aunt,

356
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,840
you didn't demand that of me.

357
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:09,440
Can you compare yourself to your sister now?

358
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,680
Every single point matters to you right now.

359
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,410
Don't find your aunt annoying.

360
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,320
Look, are you learning this instrument

361
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,920
just to avoid doing exercises?

362
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,280
I'm telling you, your mom spoils you,

363
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:20,400
but Aunt won't.

364
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,280
Alright, Sis.

365
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,520
That's all based on your experience.

366
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,560
Xiaoxing, hurry up and practice.

367
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:27,680
Once you're done, go inside and do your test papers.

368
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,120
I still have to do them?

369
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:29,840
Of course.

370
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:32,440
Cencen.

371
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:35,200
Your studies have been too heavy lately.

372
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,530
Remember what Mom said.

373
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,680
Trading your health for grades

374
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:39,760
is never worth it.

375
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,740
Mom, I'm feeling much better now.

376
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,200
And Jingdezhen has beautiful scenery.

377
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,880
The doctor even said I can stop my medication.

378
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:47,680
Right, Sis.

379
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,210
The air here is really good.

380
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,360
And for someone

381
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:52,960
to find a major they like

382
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,680
is not an easy thing.

383
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:55,960
Many people even now

384
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:57,690
don't have a direction in life.

385
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,640
Final exams are starting soon.

386
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:01,400
Just stay home and read.

387
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,440
Go out less.

388
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:03,680
Got it.

389
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:12,620
Sister,

390
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:14,540
why aren't you asleep yet?

391
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,480
I can't sleep.

392
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:17,760
What's up?

393
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,720
What's wrong?

394
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,840
Look at our Cencen.

395
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,520
She either stays out all day

396
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,040
or comes home and stays up late reading.

397
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,780
I'm really worried about her health.

398
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:39,080
Sister,

399
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,120
can you look after her forever?

400
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,840
I don't know why,

401
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:46,280
but I've been feeling a bit anxious lately.

402
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:47,720
How could you not be?

403
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,160
You worry too much.

404
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:50,360
Look here,

405
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:52,450
you have a white hair sticking out.

406
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:53,920
Where?

407
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:54,780
Right here.

408
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:55,920
Pluck it out for me.

409
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:56,640
White hairs.

410
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:58,160
You can't pluck them, I'm telling you.

411
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,820
The more you pluck, the more will grow, you know?

412
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:14,520
Master Wei, please preside over the lighting ceremony.

413
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:15,040
Please.

414
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:20,160
Pay respects to the Kiln God.

415
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:46,880
The kiln ancestors soar to the sky, and the cranes wander.

416
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,770
Protect our kiln industry,

417
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,960
to prosper forever.

418
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:54,850
Pay respects to heaven.

419
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,320
Pay respects to earth.

420
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,320
Pay respects to the Kiln God.

421
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:31,480
Push it in. Push it in.

422
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,060
Be careful. Push it in.

423
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:34,540
Lao Chen, come.

424
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:35,800
Lend a hand.

425
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:36,200
Come, come.

426
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:36,560
Come.

427
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,720
Get this ready.

428
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,560
Put the wet ones aside.

429
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:43,560
Don't put them in.

430
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,960
Even out the big pieces.

431
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:46,520
Okay.

432
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:47,200
Put it over there.

433
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,000
Give me a hand.

434
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:55,120
Add firewood.

435
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:56,320
Coming.

436
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:57,080
Come.

437
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,240
Level it out.

438
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:02,000
Watch the vent.

439
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,040
Master,

440
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:18,320
what's wrong?

441
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:19,840
I'm here.

442
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,600
I'm fine. I just dozed off.

443
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:24,840
Don't make a fuss.

444
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:25,800
Are you sure you're okay?

445
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,560
I'm fine.

446
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:27,000
Okay.

447
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:00,220
Alright, alright.

448
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:01,200
You guys,

449
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,600
you guys,

450
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,080
go back and get some rest.

451
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,160
Okay, okay.

452
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,640
Everyone, go back.

453
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,080
Thanks for your hard work, guys.

454
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:09,680
It's fine.

455
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,410
Guan Lin,

456
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:12,640
you stay.

457
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,240
Keep watch.

458
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:15,840
Hurry up.

459
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:31,540
Do you want to rest a bit later?

460
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:33,280
The smoke is heavy inside.

461
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,410
You don't look well.

462
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,320
I can't bear to rest.

463
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,320
All the changes in the kiln right now

464
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:39,760
feel so magical to me.

465
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,020
The pine resin emitted by the wood

466
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:43,320
and the fine moisture in the kiln

467
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:44,280
are combining,

468
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:47,080
soaking into the porcelain body.

469
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:47,440
Here.

470
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,720
I can't help but start imagining

471
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,440
what the natural pine ash glaze

472
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,300
will look like.

473
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,400
That's why the experienced masters know

474
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:56,480
that opening the kiln every time

475
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,140
brings a different surprise.

476
00:24:59,000 --> 00:24:59,960
Or maybe a scare.

477
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,000
Let's eat.

478
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:06,480
The food is ready.

479
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:07,000
Yeah.

480
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:08,210
Sit down.

481
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:09,800
I'm starving.

482
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:10,760
Mr. Wei isn't here yet.

483
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:12,420
He's still watching the kiln.

484
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,380
Where is my master?

485
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:18,240
He's still watching the kiln.

486
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,170
It's time to eat!

487
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,600
Master, whenever it's mealtime...

488
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:23,680
Master.

489
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:25,440
Master.

490
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,000
Master.

491
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:29,560
Mr. Wei.

492
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,080
Mr. Wei.

493
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:30,720
Call an ambulance.

494
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:31,200
Mr. Wei.

495
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:31,960
Mr. Wei.

496
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:33,080
How is he?

497
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,600
How is Mr. Wei?

498
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,800
Was he still firing the kiln?

499
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:39,840
Yes.

500
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:43,080
We advised him to come to the hospital for treatment long ago.

501
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:44,520
But he just wouldn't listen.

502
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:46,720
He didn't even let us tell you the truth.

503
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:48,720
Mr. Wei,

504
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:52,330
Mr. Guan.

505
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:53,290
Mr. Guan,

506
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,360
look at this fire.

507
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,600
Should we control it?

508
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,240
Okay.

509
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:00,720
Mr. Guan,

510
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:02,930
it rained a few days ago.

511
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,360
Look at these pieces of pine.

512
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:06,220
Is the moisture content too high?

513
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:07,160
Yes,

514
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:08,280
it is.

515
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:12,080
Mr. Wei's cancer worsened a long time ago.

516
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:13,640
Even though he looks happy all day,

517
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,560
he's actually just pushing through.

518
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:17,760
He also said his apprentices couldn't know.

519
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:18,800
If they found out,

520
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:20,840
they wouldn't focus on learning.

521
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:22,280
Then this time, it's because...

522
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:23,560
The medication I gave him

523
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:25,120
is already at the maximum dosage.

524
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:25,760
Normally,

525
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,960
just enduring the physical pain

526
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,080
drains most of his energy.

527
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:33,320
Given his current physical condition,

528
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:34,850
how can he fire the kiln?

529
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,400
Isn't it just nonsense?
